\h Ovadyah
\toc1 Ovadyah
\toc2 Ovadyah
\toc3 Ova.
\mt1 Ovadyah
\mt2 (Obadiah)
\is1 Introduction
\ip This short document was written by the prophet Ovadyah (three syllables, traditionally spelt as вҖҳObadiahвҖҷ) and is about God's judgement and punishment of EdomвҖ”the nation made up of Esau's descendants. Esau was Yacob's twin-brotherвҖ”the sons of Yitshak (вҖҳIsaacвҖҷ), however the two sets of descendants ended up as enemies. So that's why Edom's people were very glad when the Babylonian army destroyed Yerushalem in 586 before Yeshua/Jesus (B.C.), and not just that, they took advantage of the invasion to join in looting the city and help the invaders. Here, God passes on through Ovadyah the declaration that Edom will be punished and defeated and their warriors would be slaughtered without any survivors, thus allowing Yisrael/Israel to recapture their lands.
\iot Main components of this document
\io1 The punishment of Edom \ior 1-14\ior*
\io1 The day of the Master God \ior 15-21\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\rem /s1 Proud Edom Will Be Brought Low; Edom's pride and downfall
\p
\v 1 \add This is\add* the visionВҰ370208 of ObadiahВҰ370209 \add given\add* by the masterВҰ370213 Yahweh concerningВҰ370215 \add вүҲthe EdomВҰ370215 region\add*:
\s1 Coming punishment for Edom
\rem /s1 Edom's Judgment Announced; The Lord Will Punish Edom
\q1 We have heardВҰ370217 from Yahweh and a messenger has been sentВҰ370222 to the nationsВҰ370221, \add telling them:\add*
\q1 \add вүҲGet everything ready\add* then goВҰ370224 into battleВҰ370229 against \add @Edom\add*.
\m
\v 2 \add And Yahweh says to Edom:\add*
\q1 Listen,
\q1 I will make you into an insignificant nationВҰ370234.
\q1 вүҲYou'll become utterly despisedВҰ370235.
\q1
\v 3 YourВҰ370249 \add вүҲinner\add* pride has deceivedВҰ370241 you,
\q2 you who live onВҰ370243 the rocky cliffs,
\q2 вүҲwithВҰ370243 yourВҰ370249 homes up there so high.
\q1 YouВҰ370242 say \add вүҲto yourselves\add* \add that\add*
\q2 no one can bringВҰ370251 you down to the groundВҰ370252.
\q1
\v 4 IfВҰ370265 you go up highВҰ370256 like an eagleВҰ370257,
\q1 вүҲeven if your nestВҰ370263 was up betweenВҰ370260 the starsВҰ370261,
\q1 YahwehВҰ370268 declares that his \add вүҲcommand\add* can bringВҰ370265 you down from thereВҰ370264.
\b
\q1
\rem /s1 Pillage and Slaughter Will Repay Edom's Cruelty
\v 5 If \add it was\add* thievesВҰ370272 who came to destroy you in the nightВҰ370279,
\q2 (and yes, you're going to be destroyed)
\q1 they would only stealВҰ370283 what they wantedВҰ370284.
\q1 Or if \add it was\add* grape-pickers who came to you,
\q1 \add at least\add* they'd leaveВҰ370291 behind \add вүҲthe smaller grapesВҰ370287\add*.
\q1
\v 6 How Esau'sВҰ370296 \add descendants\add* will be looted.
\q1 вүҲ\add #Their\add* hiddenВҰ370298 treasuresВҰ370298 will be \add вүҲfound\add* \add and taken\add*.
\q1
\v 7 \add вүҲThose who have treatiesВҰ370306 with you\add* will force you to the borderВҰ370302.
\q1 вүҲ\add вүҲThose who talk about peaceВҰ370311\add* will deceiveВҰ370307 you.
\q1 вүҲ\add вүҲThose who eat meals with you\add* will set a trap for you.
\q1 \add вүҲYou have no idea what's about to hit you\add*.
\b
\q1
\v 8 YahwehВҰ370325 will make a declaration on that dayВҰ370321.
\q1 The wise \add people\add* of EdomВҰ370328 will be destroyedВҰ370326.
\q1 вүҲUnderstanding will disappear from Esau'sВҰ370331 hill.
\q1
\v 9 And you \add the city of\add* Teyman, yourВҰ370334 warriorsВҰ370334 will be shatteredВҰ370333,
\q1 вүҲso that everyoneВҰ370339 from Esau'sВҰ370341 hill country \add вүҲwill be slaughteredВҰ370342\add*.
\s1 The charges against Edom
\rem /s1 Edom Mistreated His Brother; Reasons for Edom's Punishment
\q1
\v 10 BecauseВҰ370344 of your violenceВҰ370344 against your brotherВҰ370345 Yacob'sВҰ370346 \add descendants\add*,
\q1 shameВҰ370348 will \add вүҲovercome\add* youВҰ370347,
\q1 andВҰ370349 you'll be \add вүҲdestroyed\add* foreverВҰ370350.
\q1
\v 11 You \add just\add* \add вүҲstoodВҰ370353 and watched\add* on that day when strangersВҰ370357 \add вүҲcarried away their\add* wealthВҰ370358.
\q1 вүҲWhen foreignersВҰ370359 entered their gatesВҰ370361 and \add вүҲtook possession\add* of YerushalemВҰ370365, you \add вүҲwished it was you doing that\add*.
\q1
\v 12 You \add вүҲshouldn't have gloated\add* over your \add вүҲcousins\add* onВҰ370377 the day of \add #theirВҰ370389\add* misfortuneВҰ370381.
\q1 вүҲAnd you \add вүҲshouldn't have celebrated\add* about the destructionВҰ370389 of the peopleВҰ370385 of YehudahВҰ370387.
\q1 You shouldn't have \add вүҲbragged\add* inВҰ370377 \add their\add* time of distress.
\q1
\v 13 You \add вүҲshouldn't have\add* gone into their city atВҰ370400 the \add вүҲtime\add* of their calamityВҰ370411.
\q1 You \add вүҲshouldn't have gloated\add*вҖ”yes, youвҖ”over their miseryВҰ370411 inВҰ370400 their \add вүҲtime\add* of disaster.
\q1 And you \add women\add* \add вүҲshouldn't have\add* grabbed their wealthВҰ370417 onВҰ370400 the day of their catastrophe.
\q1
\v 14 You \add вүҲshouldn't have\add* stood at the crossroadsВҰ370426 to \add вүҲkill those trying to escape\add*,\x + \xo 1:1-14: \xt Isa 34:5-17; 63:1-6; Jer 49:7-22; Eze 25:12-14; 35:1-15; Amos 1:11-12; Mal 1:2-5.\x*
\q1 And you \add вүҲshouldn't have handed-over\add* any survivorsВҰ370434 that you'd captured in \add their\add* \add вүҲtime\add* of troubleВҰ370436.
\s1 The punishment of nations
\rem /s1 God Will Judge the Nations; Edom Destroyed, Israel Restored
\q1
\v 15 For all the nationsВҰ370448, Yahweh's dayВҰ370441 is near,
\q1 Just as you'veВҰ370450 done, \add вүҲthe same\add* will be done to you.
\q1 вүҲYour actions will returnВҰ370454 onto your own headВҰ370455.
\q1
\v 16 Because just like how all you \add Israelis\add*\f + \fr 1:16 \ft It's not actually clear from the Hebrew who вҖҳyou allвҖҷ refers to, so the addition of вҖҳIsraelisвҖҷ is clearly an interpretive decision and other translations might differ.\f* drank \add suffering\add* on my holy mountainВҰ370462,
\q2 all the nationsВҰ370467 will drink continuallyВҰ370468.
\q1 They will drink and swallowВҰ370470 it down.
\q1 They'll become as if they'd neverВҰ370472 \add even\add* existed.
\s1 Yisrael's victory
\rem /s1 Israel's Final Triumph; The Victory of Israel
\s4 Both kingdoms
\q1
\v 17 \add вүҲButВҰ370475\add* onВҰ370475 MtВҰ370475. TsiyyonВҰ370476 (вҖҳZionвҖҷ), there'll be deliveranceВҰ370478,
\q2 andВҰ370475 it will be holy,
